# StockGuard API

StockGuard API is a robust backend system for inventory management, built with Node.js and integrated with Supabase for data persistence.

## ğŸš€ Features

- Complete inventory management
- Supplier management
- Stock movement tracking
- User authentication
- Order processing
- Location management
- Product catalog
- Customer management

## ğŸ›  Tech Stack

- Node.js
- Express.js
- Supabase
- Swagger (OpenAPI 3.0.0)

## ğŸ“‹ Prerequisites

- Node.js installed
- Supabase account
- Git

## âš™ï¸ Installation

1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/ThiagoEwer/stockguard-api.git

cd stockguard-api

npm install


## Execute
Execute the script on: src/config/SQL/DBCreations.sql in you supabase or another SGBD

Configure environment variables: Create a .env file with:
SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url
SUPABASE_KEY=your_supabase_key
PORT=3000

## Start the server:
npm run dev


## ğŸ“š API Documentation
The API documentation is available through Swagger UI at:
http://localhost:3000/api-docs


## ğŸ—„ï¸ Database Structure
The database is structured in Supabase with the following main tables:

usuari - User management
fornec - Supplier information
estoq - Stock control
movime - Movement tracking
produt - Product catalog
pedido - Order management
local - Location management
client - Customer data
Database Creation Script
The complete database creation script is available in the db-creation.sql file. This script includes:

Table creation
Foreign key relationships
Indexes
Initial data seeding
Soft delete functionality implementation

## ğŸ” Security
Authentication required for all endpoints
Soft delete implementation for data safety
Role-based access control

